spanGrp.span: Ys antepasado-wa je bete-te r Talamanka
Two of them escaped to Ujarraz.
b-ol wa a eskapa-wa-te Jie-wa t Ujarras (_) Ujarras
They brought their kids and lived;
jie-wa w yabla bet wa se-n'
they hunt pacas, peccaries and so on, and panted bananas, mandioc.
(_) jie-wa t r eree kasri bi kono bi jir bi te-g jem chom r shk bi r je bt-g je ke-g-ite
They cooked all that and raised their children that way;
they would smash the bananas so the kids could eat or drink them.
yabla a chom wtue-g-ite m-g-ite guya-l o ya-l
There they lived and worked only.
Jeska jie-wa ser-g r (hm) shkabl wa jeb
They would plant or else sometimes they went hunting and thus fed themselves.
Jie-wa mi-gu-lo jir k jir k o si no mgalela she-g-ite-n m-gu-lo r jir kt Je je wa a chewa-g jela
We grew up like that long ago.
Jie-wa jebi jiska jira sa kebi-l r ta (_) miga bete-te taran ka pe sr kn jebi
For quite sometime until now some still live like that;
Maleska maleska-wa b n ser-g jebi r
they say that when they grew up they would invite the others, and sometimes they would take us they just lived in the bush;
Pa-g-ite jela-n ji la n (_) jie-wa kebir-g-ra m-g siga-wa ki je invitarwe-g-ite migalera je sa tse-g-ite jem ere ere migale jie-wa jie-wa r se-n' k'jrga wa jeb
they did not live in houses;
jie-wa ka r sr j n
they would purify themselves and took care of things like pigs, dogs and cats, of which they had lots.
jie-wa r jir bets (_) jir knn (_) kuchi bi chichi bi michi bi ts t'
They fed the cows; they always had things to do, not like other people.
Jie-wa w baga chw jir w jir w wjeb jie-wa ka ka ka kun maleska-wa bi bi ser-g
In some cases they would take their children along to work and would teach them how to work.
Jie-wa r shkabl wajeb jem ere maleska-wa ra n yabla mi-g mi-g wa shkabl jiebi Yabla yue-g-ite shkabl jir kk
When they grew up, they would be able to harvest even if they are still little.
Jebi ra yabla degau-lo-ka keyge-ra jir jir tse-g-ka Jie-wa r yuliski-gla-wa-ra jie-wa t jir jir wakwa t tke-g-ka wakwa t jir w-g-ka
They could plant and do things by themselves, like dry-banana drink, ripe banana drink; they would make lots of chicha out of corn on the cob.
